description: Heroes glide through the sky on lightning bolts and fire. Flamboyant villains attempt daring daylight robberies. God-like alien creatures clash in epic battle over the nighttime sky. And on the dirty city streets below, Homicide Detective Christian Walker does his job. Walker is teamed up with spunky rookie Detective Deena Pilgrim to investigate murders specific to superhero cases. Investigations that takes them from the seediest underbelly a city has to offer, to the gleaming towers that are home to immortal beings. It's cops and capes like you have NEVER seen them in the surprise hit of the from super hot comic writer and EISNER award winning team of Brian Michael Bendis (Ultimate Spider-Man titles, Daredevil, Alias) and full color, art deco comic artist Mike Avon Oeming (Bluntman and Chronic, Hammer of the Gods) "Anarchy" - Part 1 It's a brand new story arc! Anarchy against powers is running rampant in the streets. A faction of young, angry, regular citizens are raging an all out war against the super-heroes that have sworn to protect them- bringing the murder of Retro Girl back into question. Plus, the strained relationship between Walker and Deena catches the attention of the ever-rabid media.
name: Anarchy (Part 1)

description: ANARCHY Part 3 of 4. Anarchy! Society is violently lashing out at their superheroes. Anti-powers groups are rising up with a series of gruesome murders against the cities most colorful capes. With Walker retired, Detective Pilgrim teams up with a new partner to investigate this murderous super-hero backlash and the people behind it.

This year Bendis scored the comic book trifecta by winning the Wizard Fan Award, Comics Buyer's Guide Fan Award and Eisner Award for 'Best Writer.' THE SHOCKING NEW POWERS STORYLINE! "Forever Man": Part One. Yeah this is where we pretty much shock the crap out of you! Powers takes a dizzying 180 degree turn and we present our largest scale storyline yet. If this storyline were a movie, it wouldn't be... because the budget would be insane. This is an epic of the largest scale. Old school Powers fans will be thrilled with the full tilt boogie, while others looking for a jump on, looking for something new in their big pile of homogenized superhero comics, will be relieved to finally find something. Notice how we didn't tell you the hook. Well, the title says a lot, and anything past that will give it away. Also, miss your letter columns? We have one of the biggest and brashest right here.

description: FOREVER PART 4 The year is 1936. Christian Walker has established himself as masked vigilante in order to fight the mob in Chicago. Aided by Albert Einstein, Walker continues to delve into his mysterious past to find the truth about his abilities. But when an age-old enemy comes for him and everything he loves, Walker must put aside his quest for truth and take up the quest for justice!

description: Variant: Whitman logo cover (see pic below).

What would you do if you found out that you were one of the most important people in the world? What would you say to someone who told you your purpose on this earth? Sara Pezzini is faced with some very difficult decisions.
After finding out more of the secrets behind the Witchblade, Sara sets her sights on learning the truth behind its existence and why she was chosen to become its present day wielder.

Sara Pezzini investigates a murder/suicide in the fashionable end of town which may be tied to recent upheavals in the netherworld, but her bosses are beginning to lose patience with her approach and conclusions.
Brace yourself for a new era of Witchblade as a few old friends return, a few new ones arrive, and Sara's life is changed forever.

As Sara and Jake continue their investigation into the brutal slayings in the mob world, they realize what's behind it all is more insidious than they thought - especially when their search leads them to the assassin.
The assassin known as Tora No Shi has waited three years for another shot at the one man who survived an encounter with him - Ian Nottingham. And this time, only one of them will make it out alive.
Part 4 of 4. From the pages of Darkness comes the enigmatic and evil Sonatine. But what does he want with Sara Pezzini and the Witchblade?
Blueish light travels through New York city, and miracles happen.
name: Endgame Prelude

description: When detective Sara Pezzini is called in to investigate a string of murders in Brooklyn, she quickly realizes there's a connection to a man she hasn't seen for some time and hoped she'd never see again.
name: A Prelude to Endgame

description:
Endgame part 2, continued from Tomb Raider #25. Sara Pezzini searches for answers to what caused the terrible fate of her friend, Lara Croft. Sara Pezzini wielding Witchblade vs. Lara Croft wielding Weave.

Available in newsstand/direct, metallic holochrome, platinum foil (same cover art on all 3 of those), JCC exclusive and numbered con exclusive.
name: Endgame, Part 2

description:
Epologue to Endgame 
Sara's problems are just beginning as an old nemesis returns that could prove more troublesome than any she's ever faced. That's right - her sister Julie is back. Also, Sara Pezzini has a talk with the EVO team.
name: Epologue to Endgame

description: An unholy evil unlike any other is ready to stake its claim into the Big Apple and Sara's in way over her head. Even with the help of the Magdalena, will it be enough?
Variant: Dynamic Forces Exclusive Gold Foil, limited 999 numbered copies.
As Sara and The Magdalena dig deeper into the mysterious homicide, they find themselves embroiled in the mysterious world of the Kabbalah.

Road Trip part 1 of 2.  
Sara tries to escape her troubles in New York City by going on a plain old fashioned road trip with nacho flavored Doritos on the seat next to her and Erasure in the stereo, but things go south when Sara picks up a young hitchicker.
name: Road Trip Part 1

description: Sara discovers her ne'er-do-well sister is romantically involved with her partner, Jake. Secondly, she gets embroiled in a mysterious murder investigation that has the whole NYPD befuddled.
name: Death Pool Part 1

description:
Death Pool Part 2

Jake’s true feelings about Sara are reveled. After being attacked by a man with super powers Sara looks to take a break but is interrupted by an old flame/enemy.
name: Death Pool Part 2

description:
Death Pool Part 3

While following leads regarding the death of a Dr. McCreary, Sara and her new partner, Frank Bernard, visit an old employer of the late doctor. When Sara realizes that it is not a hospital, but a front for a more sinister business, they pursue one of the people they had seen at the facility. During their pursuit, they are beset upon by agents of Level 42, with whom Sarah has previously had violent run ins. During the battle, Sarah takes Ian's words to heart and lets the Witchblade loose, as she never has before. Not victorious, and wounded, but alive, Sara and Frank limp back to headquarters with more questions than answers....
name: Death Pool Part 3

description:
Death Pool Part 4

Jake McCarthy’s makes some headway with personal investigation on his girlfriend, Julie Pezzini. When learning the truth about the Level 42 Sara realizes how involved she really is the current events.
name: Death Pool Part 4

description:
Death Pool Part 5

Last chance for the fans to make their decision!

Sara finds her self in trouble and must rely on the aid of a foe to survive, and the Witchblade makes move to establish itself as a play it this story arc.
name: Death Pool Part 5

description: Troy Hickman and David Nakayama, the winner of the Wizard/Top Cow intern contest, create this tale. New bad girl, Celestine, is a torn soul. Sara must stop her trail of carnage while at the same time keeping the Witchblade under her command.
name: Strenght and Weakness Part 1

description: Common Grounds writer Troy Hickman writes the tale of Celestine Abbadon for every good deed she does, she must do an equal evil act. Sara Pezzini and the Witchblade are hot on her trail, but will the Witchblade abandon Sara in her moment of need? Cover by Greg Land.
name: Strenght and Weakness Part 2

description: The carnage continues as another longstanding Top Cow character dies! Witchblade-wielder and homicide detective Sara Pezzini investigates events that will reverberate throughout the Top Cow Universe for the next year... and we're introduced to Tony Daniel's new series, Humankind, as well!
name: Signs and Portents Part 1

description: When a powerful player in the Top Cow universe is found dead, NYPD detective and Witchblade-wielder Sara Pezzini is on the case. But what Sara find goes much deeper than any routine homicide, and the reverberations will be felt throughout the Top Cow Universe for months to come!
name: Signs and Portents Part 2
